        <step1>
            <para count="1">Visually inspect all accelerator and linkage controls for proper connection and freedom of
                movement. Replace or repair as necessary.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the accelerator pedal fully depressed, the throttle control lever must be in FULL
                THROTTLE position with the lever stop screw hard against the stop on the injection pump housing.
                Override system on injection pump lever should be partially engaged. If throttle lever does not reach
                full throttle stop, adjustment of cable is required.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Override position ensures that slight wear can occur in the throttle cable assembly and the
                        control lever will still contact the high idle stop.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">* - Manual specified with latest revision</emph>
            </para>
            <para>ACCELERATOR LINKAGE</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Visually inspect the accelerator linkage to assure that it returns to idle position. Adjust as
                        required. Record results on CGED-440-*.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Adjust Linkage as Follows: (Refer to Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600510">5.10</hotlnk>).
                </emph>
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Secure the accelerator control (pedal) in the FULL THROTTLE position.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Adjust the length of the throttle control cable by turning the ball joint that connects
                    to the injection pump lever, until the high idle stop screw contacts the stop on the injection pump
                    housing. THE OVERRIDE SYSTEM SHOULD NOT BE ENGAGED.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Tighten the ball joint three full turns onto the throttle control cable to obtain the
                    proper amount of override.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Tighten the jam nut.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>A COMPLETELY BOTTOMED OVERRIDE LEVER CONDITION CAN CAUSE SEVERE DAMAGE TO THE INJECTION
                            PUMP ASSEMBLY. REPAIR OR REPLACE CONTROLS AS REQUIRED.
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">* - Manual specified with latest revision</emph>
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
